strings.Value: "Damn it! It's like I never left the tribe. How far do I have to go before I'm not running into Kellids on every hill?!"
"The past is an enchanted place. Those who run from it, run in circles. Those who would leave it behind, flee into it as it chases them."

"The more you think about it, the more confused you get. Why don't you have a drink and get some sleep. And when someone reminds you of something you'd rather forget, twist their heads off. Let them run from you, ha ha..."
"I tried to escape my past for a time, but I couldn't take a single step away. Until I realized no actual walking was necessary."
"You wouldn't meet any in Kelesh. But I don't think you'd like my tribe any better than your own."
"You wouldn't meet any in Kelesh. But I don't think you'd like my tribe any better than your own."
